  "text": "MS-BFS-Graft algorithm shows good scaling on different multithreaded and MIC architectures. Fig. 8 shows the strong scaling of the MS-BFS-Graft algorithm on Mirasol and Edison for different classes of graphs. We report the average speedup for graphs in each class with respect to the serial MS-BFS-Graft algorithm. Using all available cores (without hyperthreading), the average speedup of problems in Table 3 is 15 on Mirasol (stdev=3.5, min=9, max=21) and 12 on Edison (stdev=2, min=7, max=15). This performance is significantly better than the reported speedup (5.5Â on a 32-core Intel multiprocessor) of the PR algorithm [CITATION_1] .",
